                                                                                                                                                   42


2-PS1-2
Students who demonstrate understanding can: Analyze data obtained from testing different materials to determine which materials have the
properties that are best suited for an intended purpose.*
Clarification Statement: Examples of properties could include, strength, flexibility, hardness, texture, and absorbency.
Assessment Boundary: Assessment of quantitative measurements is limited to length.
