        Science and Engineering Practices                             Disciplinary Core Ideas                                Crosscutting Concepts
  Asking Questions and Defining Problems                LS1.A: Structure and Function                         Cause and Effect
  • Ask questions that arise from examining             • All cells contain genetic information in            • Empirical evidence is required to
      models or a theory to clarify                          the form of DNA molecules. Genes are                  differentiate between cause and
      relationships.                                         regions in the DNA that contain the                   correlation and make claims about
                                                             instructions that code for the formation              specific causes and effects.
                                                             of proteins. (Secondary)
                                                        LS3.A: Inheritance of Traits
                                                        • Each chromosome consists of a single
                                                             very long DNA molecule, and each gene
                                                             on the chromosome is a particular
                                                             segment of that DNA. The instructions for
                                                             forming species’ characteristics are
                                                             carried in DNA. All cells in an organism
                                                             have the same genetic content, but the
                                                             genes used (expressed) by the cell may
                                                             be regulated in different ways. Not all
                                                             DNA codes for a protein; some segments
                                                             of DNA are involved in regulatory or
                                                             structural functions, and some have no
                                                             as-yet known function.
